<h1>Glas3 concepts: Array</h1>
An <b>Array</b> is a concept that stores objects of the same type in a linear arrangement, but possibly indexed in a multlilinear fashion.
<h2>Requirements</h2>
The type <code>X</code> satisfies Array if and only if:
<ul>
<li><code>X</code> satisfies <a href="http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/concept/CopyConstructible">CopyConstructible</a>.
</li>
<li><code>X</code> must have the following types:
<table border="1">
<tr><th>name</th><th>type requirements</th><th>notes</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>value_type</code></td><td><code>std::is_arithmetic&lt;value_type&gt;</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>size_type</code></td><td>must be a <a href="http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/concept/SequenceContainer">SequenceContainer</a></td></tr>
</table>
<li>Given
<ul>
<li><code>x,y</code> of type <code>X</code>
<li><code>s</code> of type <code>X::size_type</code>
<li><code>i<sub>1</sub>,...,i<sub>d</sub></code> of type <code>X::size_type::value_type</code>
</ul>
the following expressions must be valid and have their specified effects:
<table border="1">
<tr><th>Expression</th><th>Return type</th><th>Semantics</th><th>conditions</th></tr>
<tr>
<td><code>X(y)</code></td><td><code>X</code></td>
<td>Copy constructor: should this be deep or shallow copy?</td><td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>x.order()</code></td><td><code>X::value_type::size_type</code></td>
<td>Return the order of <code>x</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>x.size()</code></td><td><code>X::size_type</code></td>
<td>Return the size of <code>x</code></td><td>x.size().size()==x.order()</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>x(s)</code></td><td><code>X::value_type</code></td>
<td>Return the element corresponding to the element with index <code>s</code></td><td><code>s</code> lies in the index range of <code>x</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>x(i<sub>1</sub>,...,i<sub>d</sub>)</code></td><td><code>X::value_type</code></td>
<td>Return the element corresponding to the element with indices <code>(i<sub>1</sub>,...,i<sub>d</sub>)</code></td>
<td><code>0&ge;i<sub>j</sub>&lt;x.size()[j]</code> for <code>0&ge;j&lt;x.order()</code></td>
</tr>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h2>Array in Glas3</h2>
